array function
#include&lt;iostream&gt; #include&lt;cmath&gt; using namespace std; /* looking for prime within 100. Sieve of Eratosthenes algorithm */ int main() { int sum=0, a[100]={0}; for(int i=2;i&lt;sqrt(100.0);i++) // outer loop for i[2,9] { sum=i; while(sum&lt;100)// inner loop for sum[2,99] { sum=sum+i; if(sum&lt;100) a[sum]=1; // why = ? } } for(int i=2;i&lt;100;i++) { if(a[i]==0)cout&lt;&lt;i&lt;&lt;&#34; &#34;; // why == ? } cout&lt;&lt;&#34;&#34;&lt;&lt;endl; return 0; } when a[i] = {9, 15} , how could we calculate and remove it from the array a[n]?
the details in the table as below
a[i] a[sum] a[sum + i] 2 2 {4, 6, 8, …… 98} 3 3 {6, 9, 12, 15…… 99} …… …… …… 7 7 {14, 21, 28, …… 98}
